OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FJohn Lewis back in profit  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fbut no bonus for staff     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, John Lewis has reported a return to    
OL,6, profit, but it will not pay its staff a
OL,7, bonus for the second year in a row.    
OL,9,FThe retail partnership, which also owns
OL,10,FWaitrose supermarkets, reported a      
OL,11,Fpre-tax annual profit of #56m compared 
OL,12,Fwith a #234m loss the year before.     
OL,14,FHowever, it said it would not pay a    
OL,15,Fbonus as it was increasing overall pay 
OL,16,Fand investing in the business.         
OL,18,FIn January, John Lewis said it was     
OL,19,Fplanning to cut the size of its        
OL,20,Fworkforce over the next five years.    
